summary: Good Omens & Criminal Minds Writing Prompt: Dialogue
body:
Good Omens & Criminal Minds Writing Prompt: Dialogue

In Heaven…

“You need to stop.”

“W-what?”

“Aziraphale is dead, Jacques. Do you hear me? Dead!”

“No. No he’s not. We both know Mr. Fell - I know, Aziraphael, Ann. He is trained soldier and an experienced agent. He wouldn’t just die, not without a fight.”

“It’s been 27 Earth years, Jac. What are the odds that they’re still alive without contacting the Heavenly Host? Not only that, the Host would know that he’s still alive.”

“Not if he’s been turned human.”

“…”

____________________________________________

“Philips, you need to ID your rapist.”

“Morgan…”

“I know. I know, Ezra. You don’t want to relive yesterday. I - no, we - don’t blame you. But - ”

“But I’m the only survivor, the only one who managed to escape after having been raped and shot.”

“… yeah. I’m sorry.”

“… Alright. I’ll do it. We’ve been chasing after this bastard for 2 weeks, he’ll come after me again because I escaped and capture, rape, and kill more women and men if I don’t do this.”

“Thank you, Philips. And I promise you we won’t let it come to that,” Hotch said in reply.

Ezra Philips-Young, FBI Agent, B.A.U. profiler, latest rape victim and survivor of the latest serial sexual sadist, grimly nodded her head and tried her damn hardest not to think about the last time she was in the hospital. The best and worst day of her life.

summary: Also, I spent half of my weekend with a die-hard Terry Pretchett fan... who was rather confused/shocked/irritated/amused/put...
title: Also, I spent half of my weekend with a die-hard Terry Pretchett fan... who was rather confused/shocked/irritated/amused/put your pick that... “Good Omens” was indeed written with Neil Gaiman.
body:
And that this “American Gods” TV series he enjoyed quite a lot … happen to be written by this Neil Gaiman as well.

Yep… in case you’re wondering: I put on the “Neverwhere” audiobook/BBC radio play while we transformed this IKEA madness into working furniture.

The fun you can have… and the world wasn’t even ending (even, hallelujah, it felt from time to time because IKEA & their instruction manuals ^^).
